<BaseLayout
  title="About | GNSS Calculator — Free Open-Source GNSS Tools"
  description="GNSS Calculator: free, open-source GNSS tools by Miguel González. GPS time, positioning, RINEX, NTRIP, ephemeris, spectrum and NMEA analysis."
  breadcrumbLabel="About"
>
  <h1>About GNSS Calculator</h1>

  <p>
    GNSS Calculator is a free, open-source tool for GNSS engineers and anyone
    working with satellite navigation data. Convert timestamps, transform
    coordinates, inspect NMEA logs, browse RINEX observations, connect to NTRIP
    casters, and explore GNSS signal spectra — all in the browser, with nothing
    to install.
  </p>

  <h2>Why I built this</h2>
  <p>
    During my years working with GNSS — first at GMV, then at Airbus Defence and
    Space, and later as a Product Engineer at
    <a href="https://leica-geosystems.com" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Leica Geosystems</a>
    — I found myself constantly jumping between scattered scripts and outdated
    web tools to do everyday calculations. I wanted a single, fast, reliable
    place to do them all. So I built one.
  </p>
  <p>
    This is a spare-time, one-person project. I design, build and maintain
    everything myself. If you find it useful, that means a lot.
  </p>

  <h2>About me</h2>
  <p>
    I'm Miguel González, an aerospace engineer based in Madrid. I hold a BSc in
    Aerospace Engineering (Air Navigation Systems) and an MSc in Signal Theory
    and Communications. After several years in the GNSS and space industry I
    moved into data science and machine learning, and I currently work as a
    Senior LLM Engineer at A5 Labs.
  </p>
  <p>
    You can find out more about me at
    <a href="https://www.miguel.es" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">miguel.es</a>,
    or reach out on
    <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/mgcalvo/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">LinkedIn</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>Open source</h2>
  <p>
    The full source code is available on
    <a href="https://github.com/MiguelPuntoEs/gnsscalc" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a>.
    Contributions, bug reports and feature requests are welcome.
  </p>

  <h2>Tools</h2>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 text-sm text-fg/60">
    <li><a href="/" class="text-accent hover:text-fg">GPS Time Converter</a> — convert between GPS, Galileo, BeiDou, UNIX, UTC, Julian Date and more</li>
    <li><a href="/positioning" class="text-accent hover:text-fg">Positioning Calculator</a> — ECEF, geodetic, UTM, AER, ENU, distances and bearings</li>
    <li><a href="/rinex" class="text-accent hover:text-fg">RINEX Viewer</a> — multipath, cycle slips, completeness, C/N0, sky plots and DOP</li>
    <li><a href="/ntrip" class="text-accent hover:text-fg">NTRIP Client</a> — browse casters, view mountpoints on a map, monitor RTCM streams</li>
    <li><a href="/status" class="text-accent hover:text-fg">Broadcast Ephemeris</a> — live satellite health and orbital parameters from the IGS</li>
    <li><a href="/nmea" class="text-accent hover:text-fg">NMEA Log Viewer</a> — parse GGA/RMC sentences, view tracks on a map</li>
    <li><a href="/spectrum" class="text-accent hover:text-fg">Signal Spectrum</a> — interactive PSD chart of all GNSS L-band signals</li>
    <li><a href="/antex" class="text-accent hover:text-fg">ANTEX Antenna Viewer</a> — phase center offsets and variations for receiver and satellite antennas</li>
  </ul>
</BaseLayout>
